deb-installer (26.07.1) mx; urgency=medium

  * Selected package files are checked more carefully before installation,
    with clear errors for missing, unreadable, or invalid files.
  * Package installation failures are now reported in the installer instead of
    only appearing in the terminal window.
  * Improved security checks around privileged package installation commands.
  * The installation terminal now stays open for the close prompt and handles
    package paths more safely.

 -- Adrian <adrian@mxlinux.org>  Fri, 10 Jul 2026 10:05:55 -0400

deb-installer (26.07) mx; urgency=medium

  * The install confirmation dialog now shows the full package version
    information including origin (e.g. local .deb vs. repository) and
    architecture, so you can better identify which version will be installed.

 -- Adrian <adrian@mxlinux.org>  Wed, 08 Jul 2026 00:47:13 -0400

deb-installer (26.06) mx; urgency=medium

  * The installer now automatically finds the programs it needs on your
    system and shows a helpful message if anything is missing.
  * Improved support for KDE Plasma and Wayland sessions — the installer
    now picks the right graphical tools for your desktop environment.
  * The package details section now sizes itself better to fit the amount of
    information shown.
  * If the terminal window can't open, the installer now displays a clear
    error message instead of failing silently.
  * Security improvements for package installation commands.

 -- Adrian <adrian@mxlinux.org>  Wed, 17 Jun 2026 08:54:46 -0400

deb-installer (26.04) mx; urgency=medium

  * Stop installation when the apt simulation fails and show the error details.
  * Handle local package paths with spaces and special characters correctly.
  * Improve package install confirmation details.
  * Fix startup behavior on Wayland sessions.
  * Ensure required authentication and terminal helpers are installed.
  * Update translations.

 -- Adrian <adrian@mxlinux.org>  Sun, 26 Apr 2026 00:00:00 -0400

